<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1466&amp;p=12507#p12507"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Piracy policy?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1466&amp;p=12507#p12507"><![CDATA[
The Wii Virtual Console service will allow owners of Nintendo's forthcoming Wii video game console to purchase (or rent?) restrictions-managed copies of classic video games. This will put a lot of out-of-print NES and Famicom games back into print and give publishers of those games more solid grounds to attack sites carrying pirated ROM files.<br /><br /><a href="http://forum.gbadev.org/viewtopic.php?p=81902#81902" class="postlink">Dwedit has criticized this board's stance on links to sites containing ROMs</a>, calling it even looser than that of <a href="http://boards.pocketheaven.com/" class="postlink">Pocket Heaven</a>. Is this something that we should be concerned about if we don't want publishers to attack Memblers and Parodius Networking, especially with Wii Virtual Console on the horizon? Is it time to set a solid policy for this board?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed May 03, 2006 8:13 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
